race.comment: SARRISMO (1) progressive gelding with a tidy win record. Returned from a lengthy break with a blistering on-pace win over 1300m at Hawkesbury in fast time. Sent to town when he sat off the speed as fav for a respectable second over 1400m at Rosehill in BM72 class. Ready for the mile and will prove hard to stop with the claim. WAL'S ANGELS (3) consistent on-pace gelding who deserves his shot in this tougher contest. Deep into the prep now and drops in weight after jumping in trip when a game second over 2000m at Bathurst. Back to the mile and can stalk the good tempo. Each way. SUPER SUGOI (5) from the in-form Matt Smith stable and represents good each way value fourth-up. Elected to go back from the gate when a plugging fifth over this trip at Kembla Grange. Can push forward today and play a leading role. INCEPTION (6) relished the mile when taken to the front from the awkward gate to salute over 1600m at Scone. Morgan sticks and no reason he can't win again. Something for the Multiples: GREEN SPACES (10)
